FBIS4-58697 "drnes088bb_94001" FBIS-NES-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 Inter-Arab Affairs Arab League Delegation Mission to Yemen Postponed Arab League Delegation Mission to Yemen Postponed NC0505142394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1320 GMT 5 May 94 NC0505142394 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 5 May (MENA)--The scheduled Arab League mission to Yemen to try to end the political crisis and prevent a destructive civil war has been postponed. A responsible source at the Arab League said that Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid asked Major General Sa'id Bayraqdar, assistant secretary general for military affairs, and Dr. 'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Sakit, the Arab League's expert on Arab affairs, to travel to Yemen today. But the delegation could not leave Cairo International Airport after officials said that the plane to Sanaa would not depart today following the closure of Sanaa Airport because of the deteriorating security situation.
